Circuit Breaker State Machine Diagram. Three states: CLOSED (Normal - green), OPEN (Failing - red), HALF_OPEN (Testing - yellow). Transitions: CLOSED -> OPEN (failure threshold reached), OPEN -> HALF_OPEN (recovery timeout), HALF_OPEN -> CLOSED (success), HALF_OPEN -> OPEN (failure). Annotations: "Failure Threshold: 5 errors", "Recovery Timeout: 60s", "Fallback Response in OPEN". German labels, state machine style.